div1.p: In the Circuit Court of the United States, Ninth Judicial Circuit, District of Washington. Northern Division.
In the matter of the application of Soo Hoo Wing for a Writ of Habeas Corpus on behalf of Fue Gam.

This cause having come on regularly for a hearing in the Circuit Court of the United States Ninth Judicial Circuit, holding term at Portland, District of Oregon, on the 6th day of February, 1893, and due return being made to the writ of habeas corpus herein issued; and it appearing that the said Fue Gam is unlawfully restrained of her liberty and the court being fully advised and informed in the premises, and due considera- tion had both as to the law and the facts therein, It is hereby ORDERED, ADJUDGED and DECREED that the said Fue Gam is entitled to her discharge, and that the said Fue Gam be and she is hereby released and discharged from custody, and that she go hence without day.
Done at Chambers, this 6th day of February, 1893.
United States Circuit Judge, Ninth Judicial Circuit.
In the United States Circuit Court For the District of Washington
In re Fue Gam vs. on Habeas Corpus
